						<summary>

						<p>States that, while <hi rend="bold">Chōḻa-mahārāja</hi> was ruling the <hi rend="bold">Rēnāṇḍu seven thousand,</hi> one <hi rend="bold">Bādeyya Raṭṭōḍlu</hi> consecrated a temple and his wife <hi rend="bold">Māraka[ṇa]</hi> and son <hi rend="bold">Chāmuṇḍeya</hi> put up the inscribed slab.</p>						

